@node Introduction "Introduction"
@{b}What is iTidy?@{ub}
  iTidy is a Workbench utility for tidying icons and resizing windows across entire directory trees. It solves the problem of manual, one-folder-at-a-time tidying and helps keep your Workbench neat, consistent, and recoverable.

@{b}Why use iTidy?@{ub}
  - Tidy thousands of drawers in one run
  - Fix layouts after changing fonts or screen modes
  - Repair broken or missing default tools
  - Safely undo changes with built-in backup/restore

@node Getting_Started "Getting Started"
To launch iTidy, double-click the iTidy icon from Workbench. Select the folder you wish to tidy, adjust options as needed, and click "Start". For more control, use the Advanced Settings window.

@node Main_Window "Main Window"
The main window provides quick access to the most common tidying operations:
- @{b}Folder Path@{ub}: Shows the selected folder
- @{b}Browse...@{ub}: Opens a requester to choose a folder
- @{b}Tidy Options@{ub}: Choose sort order (Folders First, Files First, Mixed)
- @{b}Start@{ub}: Begins tidying with current settings

@node Advanced_Settings "Advanced Settings"
Accessed via "More Options...". Here you can:
- Set window aspect ratio (Tall, Square, Wide, etc.)
- Choose overflow strategy (Expand Horizontally, Vertically, Both)
- Adjust icon spacing (X and Y)

@node Default_Tool_Analysis "Default Tool Analysis"
Use "Fix Default Tools..." to scan for missing or invalid default tools in WBPROJECT icons. Filter results, review tool paths, and repair broken associations easily.

@node Restoring_Backups "Restoring Backups"
If backups were enabled, use "Restore Backups..." to revert folders to their previous state. Select a backup run, review details, and restore as needed.

@node Tips_Troubleshooting "Tips & Troubleshooting"
- Always enable backups for large changes
- Use Advanced Settings for best layout results
- If icons don't open, check default tool paths
- For help, see this guide or contact the author

